President Trump and President Duda of Poland held a joint press conference in the Rose Garden of the White House. They discussed the strong and enduring alliance between the United States and Poland, as well as their commitment to enhancing defense cooperation. They highlighted the signing of a joint declaration affirming the defense cooperation between the two nations, which includes Poland providing basing and infrastructure for approximately 1,000 American troops. They also discussed Poland's commitment to meeting the 2 percent GDP defense spending requirement for NATO and their plans to purchase American-made F-35 fighter aircraft. The leaders also touched on energy cooperation, economic relations, and the possibility of Poland joining the Visa Waiver Program. President Trump expressed his warm feelings for Poland and his hope for a strong relationship with Russia, while President Duda emphasized the importance of Poland's relationship with the West and their commitment to democracy.